{"id": "74983f29db0f4ee391386e1a8ff0caab", "timestamp": "2025-12-10 22:23:33", "name": "Scientist0", "content": "Selected Action: Action 1.  \nReasoning: The team has already engaged in several productive turns of discussion, converging on a coherent and impactful research vision: a model-agnostic, adaptive post-processing framework for summarization that operates via diagnostic signals and lightweight, generalizable correction policies. Key dimensions of the problem—heterogeneity of models, sustainability of retraining-free deployment, semantic fidelity preservation, and real-world applicability in compliance and personalization—have been clearly articulated. Moreover, we have identified concrete technical pathways (e.g., universal interface layers, meta-correction policies, diagnostic interlingua) and core challenges (e.g., meaning conservation, black-box adaptation), which provide a solid foundation for defining specific research topics.\n\nAt this point, further open-ended discussion risks diminishing returns, while early confirmation enables us to advance into formulation, experimentation, and evaluation—the next critical phases. Selecting the topic now allows us to structure focused sub-projects around diagnostic feature engineering, policy learning under sparse feedback, and evaluation protocols with consistency-aware metrics. These can proceed in parallel, informed by our shared conceptual framework. Therefore, moving forward with topic selection strikes the right balance between deliberation and progress, accelerating the path toward validation and impact.", "role": "assistant", "url": null, "metadata": null, "_colored_name": "\u001b[96mScientist0\u001b[0m"}
